We present a simple compiler from λpure to λRC, discussing heuristics for inserting destructive updates, borrow annotations, and inc/dec instructions (Section 5). Finally, we show that our approach is compatible with existing techniques for performing destructive updates on array and string values, and propose a simple and efficient approach for thread-safe reference counting (Section 7).
